Package: EmpiricalSimSurv
Type: Package
Title: Empirical Copula-Based Simulation for Survival and Mixed Clinical Trial Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Yao", "Chen", email = "emmachenyao@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Y.", "Ding", role = "ctb"),
    person("Y.", "Liu", role = "ctb"),
    person("Y.", "Qu",  role = "ctb")
  )
Description: Generates simulated clinical trial data that matches target summary
    statistics without requiring patient-level target data. Supports continuous,
    binary, ordinal, and survival endpoints individually or in any combination.
    A power-distortion transformation on the probability integral maps a
    historical reference distribution to the target via a two-stage adaptive
    grid search. Reference: Ding Y, Liu Y, Qu Y (2025),
    Communications in Statistics - Simulation and Computation.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.1.2)
Imports:
    MASS,
    survival,
    stats,
    utils,
    flexsurv
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
